-- CNA Hires Macquarie’s Anderson for Mergers-and-Acquisitions Post
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-11-05T16:22:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-05/cna-hires-macquarie-s-anderson-for-mergers-and-acquisitions-post.html
CNA Financial Corp., the commercial
insurer majority-owned by  Loews Corp. (L) , hired Macquarie Group
Ltd.’s  James Anderson  to oversee mergers, acquisitions and
divestitures.  Anderson will be senior vice president of financial
planning and analysis and corporate development, the Chicago-
based insurer said today in a statement distributed by Business
Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
